## Migration Analysis

Your code has **three patterns** that break on .NET 8:

| API | Problem on .NET 8 |
|-----|-------------------|
| `Thread.Abort()` | Throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` (SYSLIB0006) |
| `Thread.Interrupt()` | Obsolete (SYSLIB0046 in .NET 9), unreliable for `WaitOne` wakeup |
| `ManualResetEvent.WaitOne()` without cancellation | Can't be interrupted cooperatively |

There's also a **race condition** in the original: if multiple items are enqueued before `WaitOne` returns, `Reset()` clears the signal and only one item is processed.

---

## Migrated Code (.NET 8)

```csharp
using System.Threading.Channels;

public class EventProcessor
{
    private readonly Channel<string> _channel = Channel.CreateUnbounded<string>();
    private Task? _runTask;
    private CancellationTokenSource? _cts;

    public void Start()
    {
        _cts = new CancellationTokenSource();
        _runTask = Task.Run(() => RunLoopAsync(_cts.Token));
    }

    private async Task RunLoopAsync(CancellationToken token)
    {
        try
        {
            await foreach (var item in _channel.Reader.ReadAllAsync(token))
            {
                Handle(item);
            }
        }
        catch (OperationCanceledException) when (token.IsCancellationRequested)
        {
            // Graceful shutdown — expected
        }
    }

    public void Enqueue(string item)
    {
        _channel.Writer.TryWrite(item);
    }

    public async Task StopAsync()
    {
        _channel.Writer.Complete();       // Signal no more items
        _cts?.CancelAfter(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5)); // Timeout fallback
        if (_runTask is not null)
            await _runTask;
        _cts?.Dispose();
    }

    private void Handle(string item) { /* ... */ }
}
```

